21
00:00:54,144 --> 00:00:56,604
Emily Stein, 177 High Street.

22
00:00:57,164 --> 00:00:58,605
Thank you.

23
00:00:58,685 --> 00:01:10,508
So I'm here as a resident of Medford, as a parent, as a nurse, as a road safety advocate, and as a victim to just address the issue of distracted driving.

24
00:01:11,248 --> 00:01:15,809
It's not just simply texting, using your phone, but it's everything.

25
00:01:15,829 --> 00:01:17,590
I feel it's an epidemic across the country.

26
00:01:18,023 --> 00:01:26,555
It goes across every age group, every race, every other demographic and region, whether it's in the city driving or out in the country.

27
00:01:28,577 --> 00:01:31,441
I have been involved in this work for the last two years.

28
00:01:32,062 --> 00:01:35,687
I know Mayor McGlynn is active in supporting what we've been doing.

29
00:01:36,556 --> 00:01:42,499
For the last two years, we've gone to Medford High School to give a presentation on distracted driving for the high schoolers.

30
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:48,061
But I view this as more of a societal problem.

31
00:01:48,121 --> 00:01:49,842
It's not just teenagers.

32
00:01:49,902 --> 00:01:51,403
Everyone says, oh, it's a teenage problem.

33
00:01:51,423 --> 00:01:52,323
They're always on the phone.

34
00:01:53,724 --> 00:01:54,664
It's every age.

35
00:01:56,645 --> 00:01:59,967
And what I'm trying to do is say, let's start with Medford.

36
00:02:00,047 --> 00:02:04,729
Let's have this be a community where we not only have gone to the high schools for several years,

37
00:02:05,925 --> 00:02:27,551
you know, on board, but to have a community-wide commitment to say, let's stop distracted driving in our community, whether we're putting up signs, whether we're having, you know, more local businesses, community members aware of it and supporting it just to build the visibility.

38
00:02:27,751 --> 00:02:33,233
I think so many people aren't aware that just talking on their phone, they could actually cause a fatal crash.

39
00:02:34,987 --> 00:02:37,248
It's something that the public needs to know a lot about.

40
00:02:37,488 --> 00:02:39,950
I've been doing this for two years because my father was killed.

41
00:02:40,790 --> 00:02:41,811
And this is why I'm here.

42
00:02:42,211 --> 00:02:43,212
And I've been doing this work.

43
00:02:43,292 --> 00:02:44,492
This is what I'm dedicated to.

44
00:02:45,453 --> 00:02:47,734
And everyone says, oh, start with your family, start with your friends.

45
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:55,798
And this is why I'm here, because I thought, let's have Medford be a place that could be a stand-up community to say, we're against this.

46
00:02:57,739 --> 00:02:59,861
I'm getting the law enforcement involved.

47
00:03:00,681 --> 00:03:04,043
I'm going to try to go to some police meetings and see what they can do.

48
00:03:05,372 --> 00:03:08,953
I mean, if you stand out in front of my house during rush hour traffic, everyone is on their phone.

49
00:03:09,133 --> 00:03:10,113
Everyone is looking down.

50
00:03:11,254 --> 00:03:12,574
And it scares me to be on the road.

51
00:03:12,614 --> 00:03:17,996
It scares me to walk down the street because I've seen a lot of bad driving and most often it's due to destruction.

52
00:03:20,556 --> 00:03:21,797
So I'm just putting it out here.

53
00:03:21,837 --> 00:03:22,917
This is my first time here.

54
00:03:22,977 --> 00:03:26,318
I just wanted to say what people think.

55
00:03:28,279 --> 00:03:32,920
I'm trying to pair up with a Gannis driving school now that they're located in the square.

56
00:03:33,835 --> 00:03:40,079
And I was talking with the owner to say, let's have a free evening session with adults.

57
00:03:40,940 --> 00:03:42,641
Anyone in the community can come.

58
00:03:43,101 --> 00:03:44,762
They can bring their child, even better.

59
00:03:45,403 --> 00:03:53,148
So that way, the family, it can be like a family agreement to say, we're going to sign a ban against phone use in the car.

60
00:03:53,388 --> 00:03:55,409
We're going to agree to do this together.

61
00:03:56,210 --> 00:03:57,511
So that's one thing we're doing.

62
00:03:58,571 --> 00:04:02,334
And then on January 7, we will be presenting at the high school.

63
00:04:03,523 --> 00:04:09,604
Mayor McGlynn, I know he's tried several times to be there in the past year, the past two years, so hopefully he will be there.

64
00:04:10,684 --> 00:04:11,785
But that will be the high school.

65
00:04:12,665 --> 00:04:26,747
I'm teamed up with the Mass Academy of Trial Attorneys, and they have been working with the mayor, and they're taking this to as many high schools across the state as they can to give a presentation that's been designed to educate on distracted driving.

66
00:04:27,707 --> 00:04:30,368
