84
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:32,694
I know in Massachusetts it's been about 7,000 presentations that have been given to high schools.

85
00:05:33,694 --> 00:05:36,036
Is there anything in the middle school or grade schools?

86
00:05:36,977 --> 00:05:37,057
No.

87
00:05:37,137 --> 00:05:43,281
And I have my three-year-old trained to say, you better put that phone down, or she looks at other cars and notices it.

88
00:05:43,822 --> 00:05:51,907
So I believe that the younger you go, they have the power to change their parents' behavior as well as just, you know, they grow up with that awareness.

89
00:05:52,328 --> 00:05:56,771
Yeah, I mean, just having two small children that are, you know, walking age,

90
00:05:57,345 --> 00:06:02,607
When we walk to school, even just from parking and walking to school, there's distracted drivers everywhere.

91
00:06:02,667 --> 00:06:07,970
So something in the grade schools would be great just to teach children to look both ways when they cross the street.

92
00:06:09,090 --> 00:06:15,393
They'll think they're OK because they're running on the sidewalk, but they're not because people are backing out of their driveways without looking.

93
00:06:15,553 --> 00:06:22,656
So I applaud you for your volunteerism and feel awful for what you've been through.

94
00:06:22,716 --> 00:06:24,597
But I think what you're doing for the community is great.

95
00:06:25,847 --> 00:06:28,909
do some personal injury work, and it's a horror story.

96
00:06:28,989 --> 00:06:30,049
It's very scary.

97
00:06:30,149 --> 00:06:35,392
I drive on 10 and 2 because I just read about what goes on and the accidents that take place.

98
00:06:35,993 --> 00:06:38,594
So we take it very seriously, I'm sure, as a council.

99
00:06:38,634 --> 00:06:44,137
And anything I personally or the council can do to help you, we're on board, absolutely.

100
00:06:44,277 --> 00:06:45,018
OK, great.

101
00:06:45,118 --> 00:06:45,698
Thanks very much.

