139
00:09:12,756 --> 00:09:17,177
Um, as someone who drives all day, uh, I think I see it more than anybody.

140
00:09:17,197 --> 00:09:24,459
I mean, people would just, I mean, it isn't so much, you know, the talking and people have Bluetooth sound, they're talking to Bluetooth, but the texting is,

141
00:09:25,107 --> 00:09:26,008
I mean, it's just ridiculous.

142
00:09:27,488 --> 00:09:28,869
And I see it constantly.

143
00:09:29,229 --> 00:09:30,930
People just texting, driving around.

144
00:09:32,711 --> 00:09:34,772
You know, people talk about distracted driving.

145
00:09:35,693 --> 00:09:37,514
We should be talking about distracted walking.

146
00:09:37,954 --> 00:09:38,755
Yes, I agree.

147
00:09:38,775 --> 00:09:40,235
Which is just as bad as you see.

148
00:09:40,536 --> 00:09:51,482
When you're downtown, people are just obsessed with their phones and they're walking on the streets and don't even, I mean, it's bad enough people aren't paying attention to the cars, but now you're not even paying attention, walking out into the streets of the cities.

149
00:09:51,502 --> 00:09:53,383
And again, I commend you for your work.

150
00:09:54,333 --> 00:09:57,115
I think the next thing should be distracted walking.

151
00:09:57,735 --> 00:10:05,419
I know London has put up cushions, like football cushions around lampposts because so many people have injured themselves walking into them.

152
00:10:05,439 --> 00:10:10,061
You see the people with the headphones and they're just walking, just not paying attention or anything.

153
00:10:10,081 --> 00:10:13,823
That's something that we are taking on as pedestrian safety as well because I think so many

154
00:10:14,786 --> 00:10:17,787
so many incidents are happening because everyone's looking down.

155
00:10:17,928 --> 00:10:21,449
And then no one knows they call it an accident because no one's at fault because they were looking down.

156
00:10:21,469 --> 00:10:22,250
They don't even know.

157
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:30,594
So what I do is when I went to speak at a medical center and I said, everyone, I'm challenging you for the next week, put your phones away, watch where you're going.

158
00:10:30,634 --> 00:10:31,974
It doesn't look at everyone out there.

159
00:10:32,034 --> 00:10:32,655
We're obsessed.

160
00:10:32,695 --> 00:10:38,577
We're obsessed with our phones and people have to understand we're not that important that we need to be in touch with everybody 24 hours a day.

161
00:10:38,837 --> 00:10:39,018
Right.

162
00:10:39,578 --> 00:10:39,918
Thank you.

163
00:10:40,198 --> 00:10:40,478
Thank you.

