171
00:11:21,044 --> 00:11:30,349
Is there any current legislation that you're tracking now or something that maybe we as a Council can review to get on board to support?

172
00:11:30,549 --> 00:11:31,010
Absolutely.

173
00:11:31,030 --> 00:11:35,893
Massachusetts, I think, since 2007 has been a textingâ€”you know, there's a texting ban.

174
00:11:36,433 --> 00:11:38,074
They keep shutting down the hands-free ban.

175
00:11:40,181 --> 00:11:41,762
I know AAA is behind it.

176
00:11:41,782 --> 00:11:43,724
There are a lot of agencies who are behind it.

177
00:11:44,365 --> 00:11:49,369
But again, it does come down to the local, the reps.

178
00:11:49,989 --> 00:11:52,271
I think it was the Senate passed, but the reps didn't.

179
00:11:52,291 --> 00:11:53,953
I forget where it was held up.

180
00:11:54,873 --> 00:11:56,174
So yes, absolutely.

181
00:11:56,235 --> 00:11:57,896
I mean, again, that's a step.

182
00:11:58,476 --> 00:12:02,480
Like I know in Canada, they have complete ban on all phone use.

183
00:12:03,063 --> 00:12:05,144
But we're a little behind.

184
00:12:05,405 --> 00:12:11,189
So a hands-free ban would be a huge help for law enforcement to at least catch people.

185
00:12:11,249 --> 00:12:15,451
Because right now, if they see someone texting, they might pull them over and they say, oh, I was just dialing a number.

186
00:12:15,852 --> 00:12:18,634
So it's hard for the law enforcement to catch people.

187
00:12:19,814 --> 00:12:30,642
So if there is a hands-free ban that passes in Massachusetts, that's one step, a big step, towards putting a stop to a lot of the incidents out there.

188
00:12:32,558 --> 00:12:34,799
As far as who to influence, I don't know.

189
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:38,861
I can do some legwork and get back.

190
00:12:39,602 --> 00:12:40,882
I know AAA is really behind it.

191
00:12:40,902 --> 00:12:48,186
Mary McGuire at AAA has been trying to track all the politicians who need to be more educated on this issue.

192
00:12:49,967 --> 00:12:50,767
But that's one step.

193
00:12:52,708 --> 00:12:54,609
Mr. President, just a thought.

194
00:12:55,369 --> 00:13:00,512
I wonder if we, as a community, can enact our own hands-free ban.

195
00:13:01,899 --> 00:13:04,360
or does that have to be done on the state level?

196
00:13:05,341 --> 00:13:08,942
I'm not sure if that's possible, but maybe we can ask a city solicitor.

197
00:13:09,763 --> 00:13:10,903
I agree with you a hundred percent.

198
00:13:10,923 --> 00:13:14,705
And I think everyone behind this reeling, uh, that, that, that drives a car.

199
00:13:15,385 --> 00:13:19,167
Um, that's all you see people on the phone constantly.

200
00:13:19,847 --> 00:13:21,208
Um, and they're not paying attention.

201
00:13:22,068 --> 00:13:26,410
