203
00:13:29,581 --> 00:13:33,881
I see people doing a host of things while they're driving.

204
00:13:34,422 --> 00:13:41,703
And sometimes I'm in my car saying, please just drive your car because they'll be in the middle of the road, not moving while traffic's going around them.

205
00:13:41,743 --> 00:13:44,344
It's, it's just, it's, it's unbelievable in my opinion.

206
00:13:44,944 --> 00:13:56,086
And, uh, I read an article, I think it was a month or two ago in the globe that the number of tickets issued, uh, we would think because we have the texting ban that there's a lot of tickets being issued.

207
00:13:56,433 --> 00:14:01,076
It's minimal, if many at all, in this commonwealth.

208
00:14:01,676 --> 00:14:09,381
And one of the reasons is, like you mentioned, it's hard to pinpoint and catch someone in the act that could be dialing the phone, make a phone call, or so forth.

209
00:14:09,401 --> 00:14:10,702
And they have every excuse in the book.

210
00:14:11,643 --> 00:14:16,606
I like the hands-free ban, although when you're talking, you can still get distracted.

211
00:14:16,646 --> 00:14:19,168
But if you're talking to a passenger, you can be distracted.

212
00:14:19,208 --> 00:14:23,871
So I think it's a step in the right direction to provide the safety we need on our streets.

213
00:14:24,375 --> 00:14:34,358
So Mr. President, if I can make that in the form of a motion, if we as a community can implement our own hands-free ban within the perimeter of our city.

